Laura Breedlove, 29, an internal resource pool registered nurse, retrieves medicine for a patient while she works a shift in the MICU, or medical intensive care unit, at the University of Louisville hospital. Jan 19, 2015 10:14 a.m. -- Louisville, KY, U.S.A -- The American Nurses Association is issuing a new policy and launching a campaign to educate hospitals and doctors about the dangers of nurse fatigue. -- Photo by Jessica Ebelhar, Freelance Jessica Ebelhar, for USA TODAY
